Genitalia (
Fig. 33
) with gonocoxa in ventral view flat, without depressions or ridges, in lateral view, rectangular, lower margin, apically with a small rounded protuberance; gonostylus narrow, rounded apically; later ramus narrow, curved apically, coextensive with gonostylus; dorsolateral ramus long, about half length of lateral ramus; aedeagus not evident.

Female . As in male except as follows: Head . Eyes at vertex separated by about one and one­half times width of ocellar tubercle; front with white hair and tomentum; occiput with pale yellow tomentum on upper half; ocellar tubercle with brown to black hair. Thorax . Mesonotum with median longitudinal cinereous stripe narrow, reaching beyond transverse suture; notum with pale yellow pile and abundant yellow tomentum; legs black, mid and hind tibiae and basitarsi ferruginous; scutellum with yellow tomentum; fore tarsi with palynophilic setae. Abdomen . Dorsum pale yellow pilose and tomentose, the latter abundant. Genitalia with posterior lobe of tergite VIII ferruginous; vaginal furca (
Fig. 4
) simple, upper half narrowly U­shaped; lower half with arms slightly curved, narrow, swollen on inner margin at apex, then flared outward at nearly a right angle.
